## Copilot Commands

### commit-ai

Automatically commit and push changes to GitHub without asking for confirmation.

**Workflow**:

1. Fetch the current git diff to understand what has changed
2. Analyze the changes and generate a concise, descriptive commit message following conventional commit format
3. Stage all changes with `git add .`
4. Create a commit with the generated message
5. Push to the current branch on GitHub

**Usage**: Simply ask "run commit-ai" or "commit-ai" to execute this workflow automatically.

**Note**: This command bypasses user confirmation, so ensure all changes are ready before invoking. The generated commit message will be descriptive and follow conventional commit conventions (feat:, fix:, refactor:, docs:, etc.).
